  "2026-07-11T23:05:05.200Z",codex-root,"Implementation start: selected after live all-status duplicate checks, full metadata/comments/notes/learnings review, GitHub issue/PR/security/dependency inspection, and SDK-first frontier reconciliation. This item is actively edited in the broad schema/config/profile/init SDK promotion bundle; unrelated open items remain unclaimed."
  "2026-07-11T23:06:26.400Z",codex-root,"Live verification correction: current main already persists all four runtime custom-field types. Isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH proof created custom_bool:boolean=true, custom_number:number=42, custom_string:string=hello, and custom_array:string_array=[a,b]; pm get returned each typed value. GH-448's customer_impact repro instead collides with a built-in create/update field and belongs to pm-b9ov; no boolean coercion code change is warranted."
close_reason: Already working on current main; four-type isolated regression proof passed and the reported key is a reserved-field collision tracked by pm-b9ov.
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/448\n\n## Problem (data loss class)\nA custom field registered `--type boolean` via `pm schema add-field` is silently never persisted when set through its auto-derived flag (`--customer-impact true` style): create/update succeeds, no warning, field absent from item and changed_fields. Boolean is one of four documented custom-field types; any boolean field (customer_impact, regression, is_blocker...) loses data on every write while reporting success.\n\n## Repro (from GH-448, pm 2026.7.4)\nfresh tracker -> `pm schema add-field customer_impact --type boolean --commands create,update` -> `pm create ... --customer-impact true` -> field missing.\n\n## Definition of done\nBoolean custom fields persist through create/update (coercion fixed); regression spec across all four field types; silent-drop path converted to hard error for unknown/uncoercible custom values; verified in sandbox from packed tarball."
